The paper discusses the concept of abstraction in visualization, which is a key topic in computer graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of topological abstraction (cs.CV) and the cognitive and perceptual qualities of the beholder (cs.MM), which are relevant to computer vision and multimedia. Finally, the paper discusses how visual abstraction can be used to produce effective and informative visual representations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
